8.16

beta0: the part of intercept of the function

beta2: If x2=0, the intercept is beta0. If the x2=1, the intercept will be beta0+beta2.

beta1: The slope of the function. If the x1 increase one unit, the y will increase beta1 unit.

Epsilon.i: Random error term and follow the N distribution in linear regression assumption.

#F test
dropx2<- lm(y~x1)
anova(dropx2,fit)
## Analysis of Variance Table
## 
## Model 1: y ~ x1
## Model 2: y ~ x1 + x2
##   Res.Df    RSS Df Sum of Sq      F Pr(>F)
## 1    118 45.818                           
## 2    117 45.577  1   0.24071 0.6179 0.4334
n=dim(data)[1]
p=3
g=1
a=0.01
qf(1-a,p-1-g,n-p)
## [1] 6.856564

H0:

reduce model: E{y}=beta0+beta1*x1

Ha:

full model: E{y}=beta0+beta2x2+beta1x1

RR: F>F(1-a,p-1-g,n-p)

F=0.6179<F(1-a,p-1-g,n-p)=6.856564

Thus, we conclude H0 and x2 can be dropped.

residual.y.x1.x2<-fit$residuals 
x1x2<-x1*x2
plot(x1x2,residual.y.x1.x2,xlab = "x1x2",ylab = "residual", pch=19)
abline(h=0)

With the increase of x1x2, the residual has a trend to increase not scattering randomly around zero. Thus, there is interaction term in model.

# F test
anova(fit,fit.interaction)
## Analysis of Variance Table
## 
## Model 1: y ~ x1 + x2
## Model 2: y ~ x1 + x2 + I(x1 * x2)
##   Res.Df    RSS Df Sum of Sq      F  Pr(>F)  
## 1    117 45.577                              
## 2    116 43.506  1    2.0713 5.5226 0.02046 *
## ---
## Signif. codes:  0 '***' 0.001 '**' 0.01 '*' 0.05 '.' 0.1 ' ' 1
a1=0.05
p.8.20b=4
g.8.20b=2
qf(1-a1,p.8.20b-1-g.8.20b,n-p.8.20b)
## [1] 3.922879

H0:

reduce model: E{y}=beta0+beta1x1+beta2x2

Ha:

full model: E{y}=beta0+beta1x1+beta2x2+beta3x1x2

RR: F>F(1-a1,1,116)

F=5.5226>F(1-a1,1,116)=3.922879

Thus, we reject H0 and conclude Ha. The interaction cannot be dropped.

The x2 has a corelation with x1 when x2=1 and their interaction will effect the estimation of y.

8.21

When x2=1, x3=0 which means wearing hard hat,

E{Y}=beta0+beta2+beta1*x1

When x2=0, x3=1 which means wearing bump cap,

E{Y}=beta0+beta3+beta1*x1

When x2=0, x3=0 which means wearing nothing,

E{Y}=beta0+beta1*x1

H0: beta3=0

Ha: beta3<0

With juding the p-value or t-value, get the conclude.

H0: beta2=beta3

Ha: beta2beta3
